nhc_headline: ...OCTAVE STILL A TROPICAL STORM BUT LIKELY TO DISSIPATE ON THURSDAY...
summary: ...OCTAVE STILL A TROPICAL STORM BUT LIKELY TO DISSIPATE ON THURSDAY... As of 2:00 PM PDT Wed Oct 08 the center of Octave was located near 15.8, -115.1 with movement ENE at 12 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1002 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 45 mph.
